Powered by RubiQube Ad Network LAGOS – The 19th edition of GOtv Boxing Night will hold at the Indoor Sports Hall of the National Stadium, Lagos, on Sunday, 14 July. This was announced by FlyKite Promotions, organisers of the event, at a press conference in Lagos on Tuesday. GOtv Boxing Night 19 will be headlined by the international welterweight challenge duel between Rilwan Babatunde of Nigeria and Daniel Lartey of Ghana. The event will also feature six domestic bouts potentially explosive bouts, one of which will see Tope Agboola face reigning African Boxing Union (ABU) lightweight champion, Oto Joseph in a national challenge duel. Also in action will be current West African Boxing Union (WABU) lightweight champion, Rilwan Oladosu, who takes on Hammed Ganiyu. The event will equally see former ABU featherweight title champion, Waidi Usman, return to action when he faces Taiwo Agbaje in a national challenge contest. Another featherweight challenge clash will see Kazeem Oliwo square up to Tope Musa. In the light welterweight division, Akeem Olaiwola will face Waheed “Showmax” Shogbamu, while Adeyemi Adekanla will take on Isaac Chukwudi.